    <briefdescription>
<para>Computes values of splines at particles in 3D. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>In Finite Difference GEMPIC formalism components of forms in the de Rham diagram are products of node centered splines of the form <formula id="2">$S^d(x_i-x_p)$</formula> of degree d and cell centered splines of the form <formula id="3">$S^{d-1}(x_{i+\frac{1}{2}}-x_p)$</formula> of degree d-1 <parameterlist kind="templateparam"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>degx</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Spline degree in x </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>degy</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Spline degree in y </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>degz</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Spline degree in z </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
